```
Implement `restore_curwin` so it attempts to `win_goto` the old `curwin` and return.

The checks are pretty similar to what's needed for splits; maybe some of this can be de-duplicated if it doesn't make things look worse?

Also the `can_move` check has to be repeated like I've done here; autocommands may have made the window external via `<C-W>ge` or similar, for example. (May be a bug that the repeated check was missing for splits...? :melting_face:)

